summary: this isn’t ceo!harry (who i love more than anything, your writing about that concept clear my acne and make my day not so crappy...
question: this isn’t ceo!harry (who i love more than anything, your writing about that concept clear my acne and make my day not so crappy ✨) but imagine best friend!harry who has to ‘interview’ anyone who wants to take you out, their name, address, job, etc... and giving them a firm talk, the whole “what are your intentions...” like an older brother would to his little sister’s date (i keep thinking back to when harry had to keep an eye on gemma because she was on a date at apple music festival)
answer:
before i literally do this one that is killing me i just wanna say how much i love you and how much honored that ceo!harry does that to you???? :’)


“what are your intentions?”

harry’s voice boomed in the start of his sentence as he sat across the person who you introduced to him one time who you were seeing, and after further snooping on your phone when he borrowed it to say he only wants to play a game, he was actually looking at your messages and getting the number of that actual person, did his research, and called them over to his house.

but you don’t need to know that.

“i-i just wanna date her.”

“ah, date but not love? loophole. caught you.”

harry rolls his eyes at the person sitting on his chair as he sits parallel to it, crossing his arms across his chest with a glare and it makes the guest shift in their seat.

“n-no! love too, of course. and date.”

“the use of ‘of course’ and ‘too’? you played yourself.”

he chuckles, shaking his head and he gives a look of daringness to the someone who you claim makes you happy, but it hasn’t been a week yet so of course he’d be wary (it could be less than a minute and he’s already wary) immensely, not wanting you to be hurt.

harry grabs the notebook and the pen on his side, clearing his throat, opening the crisp pages and clicking the pen before he looks at that someone sternly, raising his eyebrow and tilting his head.

“two-minute speech of you summarizing your job, lifestyles, living situation and true intentions. after that, a quiz of everything y/n likes and doesn’t. go.”
